title: America’s First Spacewalk
description: NASA astronaut Ed White, pilot of the Gemini IV mission, floats in space on June 3, 1965, while performing the first spacewalk by an American. As White floated outside the spacecraft, he used a Hand-Held Maneuvering Unit, informally called a “zip gun.” The device, seen in White’s right hand in this image, expelled pressurized oxygen […]
author: Monika Luabeya

title: Future Engineers Shine at NASA’s 2025 Lunabotics Robotics Competition
description: And the winner is… the University of Utah in Salt Lake City. The Utah Student Robotics Club won the grand prize Artemis Award on May 22 for NASA’s 2025 Lunabotics Challenge held at The Astronauts Memorial Foundation’s Center for Space Education at the Kennedy Space Center Visitor Complex in Florida.  “Win was our motto for the […]
author: Elyna Niles-Carnes

title: Why it's taking a century to pin down the speed of the universe
description: The Hubble constant, a set number that connects a galaxy’s speed to its distance from Earth and tells us how fast the universe is expanding, was first described more than a hundred years ago – but astronomers have debated it ever since

title: Private ispace Resilience probe will attempt lunar landing this week
description: If successful, Resilience will be only the third private spacecraft to complete a landing on the moon, and the first operated by a non-US company

title: Aliens, asteroid mining … and Mars births? Royal Society envisions next 50 years in space
description: UK needs a ‘clear national ambition’ to avoid missing out as science changes rapidly, Space: 2075 report warnsHumanity must prepare for a sweeping revolution as nations and companies gear up to build moon bases, space stations and orbiting factories, and uncover evidence – if evidence is out there – that we are not alone in the universe.A horizon-scanning report from the Royal Society envisions a new era of space activities that will reshape the world, including clean energy beamed to Earth, robots that mine asteroids or recycle dead satellites, and manufacturing plants that circle the planet churning out products labelled “Made in Space”. title: What time will Japan's ispace Resilience probe land on the moon on June 5?
description: The Japanese company ispace will attempt to land its Resilience lander on the moon on June 5. Here's what time and how to watch it live.

title: 'Starship in space': See amazing photos from SpaceX megarocket's Flight 9 test mission
description: SpaceX's Starship megarocket tends to put on a show, and its latest test flight was no exception. See some gorgeous photos of the vehicle in space on Flight 9.
